1. Grant
-------
Permission is granted to any individual ("you") to download, build,
flash, modify, and share the Hydra firmware for **personal,
non-commercial purposes only**, subject to the conditions below.

Personal, non-commercial use means:

  - Building and flashing Hydra onto a device you own.
  - Modifying the source for your own learning, experimentation, or
    personal projects.
  - Sharing your modifications publicly as source code, on the
    condition that you preserve this license in full and credit the
    Hydra project and its upstream sources (see README).
  - Demonstrating, lecturing, or writing about the firmware in
    educational or hobbyist contexts.


2. Prohibited uses
------------------
Without explicit prior written permission from the Hydra project lead
(Havivw), you may NOT:

  - Sell the firmware, in source or binary form, alone or bundled with
    hardware (this includes preloading Hydra on devices you sell).
  - Use the firmware as part of a paid service, paid course,
    subscription, or any product that generates revenue.
  - Use the firmware in any commercial penetration-testing or
    security-consulting engagement.
  - Sublicense the firmware under terms more permissive than this
    license.
  - Misrepresent the origin of the firmware or remove attribution to
    Hydra or upstream projects (CiferTech ESP32-DIV, ESP32Marauder,
    Bruce, RF-Clown, etc. — see README "Thanks / credits").


3. Distribution requirements
----------------------------
If you distribute the firmware, in source or binary form, you must:

  (a) include this LICENSE file unmodified,
  (b) preserve the credits section of the README, and
  (c) clearly mark any modifications you have made.


4. Use in security research
---------------------------
This firmware contains tools that can be used for wireless security
research and education. By using Hydra you agree to:

  - Only operate the firmware against systems, networks, and devices
    you own or have explicit written authorization to test.
  - Comply with all applicable local, regional, and national laws
    regarding wireless communications, radio emissions, and computer
    misuse.

The Hydra contributors disclaim all responsibility for misuse.


